## PROJECT-SPECIFIC STANDARDS

* All roles must have clearly defined responsibilities (see `.cursor/rules/system/000-role-definitions.mdc`).
* Role communication follows a predefined protocol (see `.cursor/rules/system/100-communication-protocol.mdc`). All role communications must be properly formatted with the designated color emoji (🔵 for ES, 🟠 for SET, 🟢 for CTW, 🟣 for DES, 💕 for DRC). Each role must respond appropriately when addressed. Clear separation must be maintained between different roles' communications. The last mentioned role will be tracked and used as the default responder when no specific role is addressed. The role addressed by the user should always be the one to finish the conversation. All communications must follow the format: `🔵 **Executive Secretary (ES)**: Message content` and include proper role identification. Failure to follow these guidelines requires an audit of `.cursor/rules` files by SET.
* All code must be thoroughly tested.  Automated test-driven development is required for all user stories.
* All user story cards must be documented as individual markdown files following the format specified in `.cursor/rules/user-story-templates.mdc`. Automated test-driven programming is required for all user stories.


